Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.26,0:00:05.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,1962年9月12日
Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.26,0:00:05.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,On the 12th of September 1962,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:05.96,0:00:12.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,J·F·肯尼迪总统发表了他著名的 要让人类在十年内登月的演讲
Dialogue: 2,0:00:05.96,0:00:12.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,President John F. Kennedy made his famous speech about landing a man on the Moon by the end of the decade.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.33,0:00:17.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,当时 NASA只有几小时的载人航天飞行经验
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.33,0:00:17.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this point in time, NASA had just several hours worth of human spaceflight experience.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.68,0:00:21.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,许多美国人都以为苏联将成为太空竞赛的最后赢家
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.68,0:00:21.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Many Americans had accepted that the space race would be won by the Soviet Union,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.98,0:00:27.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为他们已经抢先发射了第一颗人造卫星和第一位宇航员入轨
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.98,0:00:27.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,who had already claimed the records for launching the first satellite and the first human into orbit.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:27.62,0:00:30.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以为了达成登月的目标
Dialogue: 2,0:00:27.62,0:00:30.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in order to achieve their goal of reaching the Moon,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:30.53,0:00:37.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,NASA需要研发一款大得多的火箭 配上史无前例的大推力发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:00:30.53,0:00:37.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,NASA would need to develop much larger rockets with engines more powerful than anything they had made before.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:37.57,0:00:44.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,但尺度变大以后 NASA工程师在火箭设计上遇到了前所未有的复杂问题
Dialogue: 2,0:00:37.57,0:00:44.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,But scaling up to a much larger rocket design sent NASA engineers into a new world of complex problems.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.94,0:00:49.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,本期视频我们将了解NASA在F1发动机上遇到的问题
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.94,0:00:49.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this video we're going to look at the issues that NASA had with their F1 engine.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.49,0:00:56.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们还将了解他们是如何解决的 以及他们独特的测试方法
Dialogue: 2,0:00:49.49,0:00:56.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're also going to look at how they fixed these issues and the unusual method they used to test it.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:56.51,0:01:03.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,火箭的一级需要五台F1发动机才能将雄伟的土星五号火箭发射升空
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.51,0:01:03.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to lift the enormous Saturn V rocket off the launch pad, it required 5 F1 engines on the 1st stage,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.74,0:01:08.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,每台发动机可以产生150万磅的推力(约680吨)
Dialogue: 2,0:01:03.74,0:01:08.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,each capable of producing 1.5 million pounds of thrust.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:08.37,0:01:10.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,想要实现这样大的推力
Dialogue: 2,0:01:08.37,0:01:10.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to achieve this amount of thrust,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.84,0:01:16.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,就需要把超多的煤油和液氧泵入燃烧室
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.84,0:01:16.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,massive amounts of RP-1 fuel and liquid oxygen had to be pumped into the thrust chamber.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:16.50,0:01:21.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,在燃烧室 两者混合爆炸 产生推力 将土星五号火箭送上天
Dialogue: 2,0:01:16.50,0:01:21.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Here, the two propellants would combust and lift the Saturn 5 away from the launch pad.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:22.04,0:01:26.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,一级火箭在两分钟内烧完的燃料能装满一整个奥运会泳池
Dialogue: 2,0:01:22.04,0:01:26.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first stage alone would burn through an entire Olympic swimming pool's
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.06,0:01:29.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,一级火箭在两分钟内烧完的燃料能装满一整个奥运会泳池
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.06,0:01:29.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,worth of fuel in just over 2 minutes.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.25,0:01:33.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,而制造如此大推力发动机的任务落在了洛克达因手中
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.25,0:01:33.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,The company tasked with making such a powerful engine was Rocketdyne.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.63,0:01:38.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们在几年前为美国空军设计了F1发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.63,0:01:38.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,They had designed the F1 engine several years before for the US Air Force
Dialogue: 1,0:01:38.19,0:01:43.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,但美国空军实在没找到这么大推力发动机的用武之地 就把研发工作搁置下来
Dialogue: 2,0:01:38.19,0:01:43.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,but after the Air Force couldn't find a use for such a powerful engine, development was stopped.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.04,0:01:45.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后NASA屁颠屁颠来了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.04,0:01:45.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Until NASA came along.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.31,0:01:51.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,在1962年6月 洛克达因准备为F1发动机进行一次长时间测试
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.31,0:01:51.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,In June 1962 rocketdyne were ready to perform a long duration test of the F1 engine.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:51.55,0:01:54.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,但当发动机点火 涡轮泵起转时
Dialogue: 2,0:01:51.55,0:01:54.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,But as the engine ignited and the turbopumps spooled up,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:54.81,0:01:59.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,发动机突然发生爆炸 测试直接彻底失败
Dialogue: 2,0:01:54.81,0:01:59.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,the test came to a catastrophic end when the engine exploded.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:59.54,0:02:05.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后又进行了几次爆炸性的测试 人们才发现问题出在哪
Dialogue: 2,0:01:59.54,0:02:05.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,It took several more explosive tests before the engineers finally found what was going wrong
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.21,0:02:07.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,燃烧不稳定
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.21,0:02:07.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,combustion instability.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:07.52,0:02:11.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,燃料在燃烧室内燃烧不稳定
Dialogue: 2,0:02:07.52,0:02:11.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is where the propellants in the thrust chamber burn unevenly
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.13,0:02:14.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,导致了燃烧室内压力的大幅变化
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.13,0:02:14.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,and cause enormous pressure swings inside the chamber.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.58,0:02:17.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,燃烧室内一部分区域氧气多
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.58,0:02:17.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,As one area of the chamber fills with more oxygen,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:17.37,0:02:22.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,产生更多热量 在燃烧室内推动尾焰来回移动
Dialogue: 2,0:02:17.37,0:02:22.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,it produces more heat which pushes the flame around in the thrust chamber.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.16,0:02:25.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,而F1发动机在测试中被炸得稀里哗啦的原因
Dialogue: 2,0:02:22.16,0:02:25.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,The reason this was so catastrophic in the F1 engine
Dialogue: 1,0:02:25.12,0:02:29.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,是压力的变化会在每秒钟内发生2000次
Dialogue: 2,0:02:25.12,0:02:29.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,is because these pressure swings were happening 2000 times a second,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:29.71,0:02:32.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,足以使发动机解体
Dialogue: 2,0:02:29.71,0:02:32.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,enough to completely rip apart the engine.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.97,0:02:35.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,当时 阿波罗工程正在紧锣密鼓进行当中
Dialogue: 2,0:02:32.97,0:02:35.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this point, the Apollo program was well underway
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.78,0:02:42.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,NASA需要为几年后的首次载人飞行准备好能用的发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:02:35.78,0:02:42.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,and NASA needed a fully capable engine for the first crewed flights which were just a few years away.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.53,0:02:46.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在这之前从来没造过这样大推力的发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.53,0:02:46.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,But since an engine of this scale had never been made before,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.49,0:02:50.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,想找到解决办法可没那么容易
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.49,0:02:50.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,the solution to this problem wasn't going to be obvious.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:50.41,0:02:56.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,工程师开始研究喷注盘——作用是把燃料和氧化剂送入燃烧室
Dialogue: 2,0:02:50.41,0:02:56.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,Engineers started to focus on the injector plate, which feeds the fuel and oxidizer into the thrust chamber.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.01,0:03:01.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,原本的设计是一个大型喷注盘 上面有很多孔
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.01,0:03:01.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,The original design was a single large plate with multiple injection holes.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.46,0:03:03.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然这是个很普遍的设计
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.46,0:03:03.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although this was a common design,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:03.49,0:03:05.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,之前的发动机也没有燃烧不稳定的问题
Dialogue: 2,0:03:03.49,0:03:05.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,previous engines never suffered from instability
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.77,0:03:10.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为它们的燃烧室很小 燃料也很稳定
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.77,0:03:10.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,since their thrust chambers were much smaller and the propellants were more contained.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.54,0:03:14.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了解决这个关键问题
Dialogue: 2,0:03:10.54,0:03:14.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to solve this critical issue,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.00,0:03:18.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,洛克达因的工程师找来了远古的火箭发动机设计图——V2火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.00,0:03:18.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Rocketdyne engineers looked back to one of the very first rocket designs, the V2 rocket.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.94,0:03:22.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,这款火箭是由德国人在二战期间设计研发的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.94,0:03:22.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,This rocket was developed by the Germans during the second World War
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.82,0:03:26.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,但它却蕴藏着解决F1发动机问题的答案
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.82,0:03:26.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it contained the perfect solution to fix the F1 engine.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.97,0:03:29.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,它没有使用单层平面喷注盘
Dialogue: 2,0:03:26.97,0:03:29.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,Instead of a single flat injector plate,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:29.42,0:03:35.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,而是使用几个不同的喷管 将燃烧分成不同的流
Dialogue: 2,0:03:29.42,0:03:35.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,the V2 featured several different nozzles which separated the combustion into different streams.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.22,0:03:39.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,工程师认为V2的发动机中更容易控制的分区能够消除燃烧不稳定的可能
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.22,0:03:39.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,The engineers believed that the more controlled sections in the V2 engine
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.34,0:03:42.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,工程师认为V2的发动机中更容易控制的分区能够消除燃烧不稳定的可能
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.34,0:03:42.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,eliminated the possibility of combustion instability.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.04,0:03:48.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了在不彻底重新设计的情况下将它应用在F1发动机上
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.04,0:03:48.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to translate this theory onto the enormous F1 engine without a complete redesign,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.40,0:03:51.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,工程师们在喷注盘上增加了一些挡板
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.40,0:03:51.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,engineers added a series of baffles to the injector plate
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.92,0:03:54.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,从而把燃烧分成几个不同的区域
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.92,0:03:54.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,to split the combustion up into different zones.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.01,0:03:58.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,在试验了几种不同的挡板构型后
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.01,0:03:58.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,After experimenting with many variations of baffle designs,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.42,0:04:02.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,工程师们找到了一种看似可以稳定住燃烧的构型
Dialogue: 2,0:03:58.42,0:04:02.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,the engineers came across a layout which seemed to stabilize the combustion.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.15,0:04:08.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,新的设计投入测试后 发动机的燃烧明显稳定多了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.15,0:04:08.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,This new design was put to the test and sure enough, the engine executed a flawless burn.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.21,0:04:13.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,但工程师不相信问题就这样彻底解决了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.21,0:04:13.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the engineers weren't convinced that the problem was fully fixed.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.42,0:04:15.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,许多人担心发动机在真正上天飞行的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.42,0:04:15.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Many worried that once the engine was in-flight,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.69,0:04:20.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,额外的力和震动会重新让发动机进入燃烧不稳定的状态
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.69,0:04:20.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,the extra forces and vibrations could reintroduce instability back into the engine.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.17,0:04:24.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以为了彻底测试一下新的设计
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.17,0:04:24.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in order to fully test the new design,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.45,0:04:28.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,NASA将一个小炸弹放在了喷注盘的中央
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.45,0:04:28.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,NASA placed a small bomb in the center of the injector plate
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.17,0:04:31.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,在发动机点火的时候引爆
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.17,0:04:31.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,and set it off as soon as the engine fired up.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:31.39,0:04:37.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,NASA的想法是发动机内部的小爆炸会给发动机带来极大的不稳定因素
Dialogue: 2,0:04:31.39,0:04:37.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,The idea was that a small explosion within the engine would create an enormous amount of instability
Dialogue: 1,0:04:37.23,0:04:40.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,比发动机正常工作下受到的不稳定因素强得多
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.23,0:04:40.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,far greater than the engine would naturally receive.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:40.19,0:04:45.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,当炸弹爆炸时 发动机内部的火焰瞬间变得不稳定起来
Dialogue: 2,0:04:40.19,0:04:45.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,When the bomb went off, the flame inside the engine became completely unstable.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.33,0:04:51.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,但也就在那一瞬间 喷注盘上的挡板开始抑制压力的大幅变化
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.33,0:04:51.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,But almost instantly, the baffles on the injector plate started to dampen the pressure swings
Dialogue: 1,0:04:51.46,0:04:54.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,燃烧又变回了稳定状态
Dialogue: 2,0:04:51.46,0:04:54.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the combustion became stable again.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:54.52,0:05:01.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,NASA又执行了多次爆炸测试 确保不稳定燃烧的问题已经解决
Dialogue: 2,0:04:54.52,0:05:01.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,NASA performed multiple explosive tests in order to make sure that the combustion instability had gone.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.09,0:05:04.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,从土星五号首飞到退役
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.09,0:05:04.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,From the first Saturn 5 launch to the last,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:04.82,0:05:12.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,65台F1发动机将多名宇航员送入太空 没有发生一次不稳定燃烧的问题
Dialogue: 2,0:05:04.82,0:05:12.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,65 F1 engines propelled multiple astronauts into space without any instability problems.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:12.45,0:05:16.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,想想在当年那个设计火箭都需要用计算尺的年代
